Zer0pa Energy — internal research workstream

Copyright (c) 2026 Zer0pa.

This repository is proprietary internal research infrastructure. Source code, schemas,
fixtures, and decision documents are not licensed for redistribution outside the Zer0pa
organisation without written permission.

Adapter modules and schemas in this repository wrap and call third-party libraries that
ship under their own licenses (Apache-2.0, BSD-3, MIT, LGPL-3, GPL-2/3, etc.). Each
upstream license is recorded in `sources_log/license_findings.jsonl` and enforced by
the `energy_pipeline.l6` license-promotion gate. No third-party tool is assumed to be
permitted for any use case beyond what its own license grants.

Any production deployment must:

- Enumerate every adapter touched and verify its license class against
  `sources_log/license_findings.jsonl`.
- Refuse class C/D/E backends in `scientific` mode without an explicit
  `kg://license-grant/<tool>` evidence record.
- Carry the boundary block (see `BOUNDARY.md`) verbatim in every artifact.

Outputs of this pipeline are research artifacts. They do not constitute regulatory,
clinical, safety, or operational guarantees and may not be used for defence or weapons
applications.
